  - STATE_UPDATE: {'last_reflection_result': "## Post-Mortem Analysis Summary\n\n### Solved Problems\nNone - this is the first real build attempt (Attempt 1 crashed before applying any fix).\n\n### Unsolved Problems\n**Go 1.25+ toolchain overlay incompatibility with `go-118-fuzz-build`**\n\nThe error is:\n```\ngo: overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.\n```\n\n### Root Cause\nThe `go-118-fuzz-build` tool (used by `compile_native_go_fuzzer_v2`) creates an overlay JSON that replaces `testing/fuzz.go` in the Go toolchain. In Go 1.25+, the toolchain is stored under `GOMODCACHE` (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@...`), and Go's overlay mechanism explicitly refuses to replace files under GOMODCACHE.\n\n### Lesson Learned\nThe `go-118-fuzz-build` tool is incompatible with Go 1.25+ when the toolchain is managed via GOMODCACHE. The fix is to install an older Go version (1.24.0) in the Dockerfile and set `GOTOOLCHAIN=local` to prevent Go from downloading a newer toolchain.\n\n### Deterioration Score: **5** (Stagnant)\n- Step 1 (Official List): Failed - compilation error\n- Step 2 (Infra Compliance): Failed - same error\n- No regression from previous attempt (Attempt 1 crashed before building)\n\n### Backtracking Check\n- ❌ Complexity Overload: No fix was applied yet\n- ❌ Logical Loop: No previous successful fix to compare\n- ❌ Strategy Exhaustion: Only 1 real attempt\n- ❌ High Deterioration: Score 5 < 7\n\n**Decision: Continue with the current approach** - Apply the Dockerfile patch to install Go 1.24.0 and set `GOTOOLCHAIN=local`."}
